  <entry>
    <title>“从入门到精通”的笔记</title>
    <url>/2020/08/19/%E4%BB%8E%E5%85%A5%E9%97%A8%E5%88%B0%E7%B2%BE%E9%80%9A/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<p>由于本人一直是英语苦手，从初中英语就不好，现在马上上研究生了，英语还是搞不清楚。发现自己语法实在是有问题，所以找来这个系列的英语语法课程，就在这里记一下自己的笔记。</p>
<h1 id="语法入门"><a href="#语法入门" class="headerlink" title="语法入门"></a>语法入门</h1><p>什么是语法？</p>
<ul>
<li>A set of conventions and rules that govern language</li>
<li>context-dependent</li>
</ul>
<h1 id="名词"><a href="#名词" class="headerlink" title="名词"></a>名词</h1><h2 id="名词入门-the-Nouns"><a href="#名词入门-the-Nouns" class="headerlink" title="名词入门/ the Nouns"></a>名词入门/ the Nouns</h2><p>The noun is bascally anything, include people, places, things, ideas</p>
<h3 id="eg"><a href="#eg" class="headerlink" title="eg:"></a>eg:</h3><p>This is <strong>Raul</strong>.</p>
<p>He is from <strong>Argentina</strong>.</p>
<p>He is a <strong>penguin</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>Raul</strong> has big <strong>dreams</strong>.</p>
<h2 id="单数名词和复数名词入门-Singular-and-Plural-Nouns"><a href="#单数名词和复数名词入门-Singular-and-Plural-Nouns" class="headerlink" title="单数名词和复数名词入门/ Singular and Plural Nouns"></a>单数名词和复数<strong>名词</strong>入门/ <strong>Singular</strong> and <strong>Plural</strong> <strong>Nouns</strong></h2><p>复数名词多以“s”结尾，来源于拉丁文，意思是“Plus”。</p>
<h3 id="eg-1"><a href="#eg-1" class="headerlink" title="eg:"></a>eg:</h3><table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="center">regular</th>
<th align="center">dog</th>
<th align="center">dog<strong>s</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody><tr>
<td align="center"></td>
<td align="center">cat</td>
<td align="center">cat<strong>s</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"></td>
<td align="center">dinosaur</td>
<td align="center">dinosaur<strong>s</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"></td>
<td align="center">whale</td>
<td align="center">whale<strong>s</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center">irregular</td>
<td align="center">leaf</td>
<td align="center">leaves</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"></td>
<td align="center">child</td>
<td align="center">children</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"></td>
<td align="center">fungus</td>
<td align="center">fungi</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"></td>
<td align="center">mouse</td>
<td align="center">mice</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"></td>
<td align="center">sheep</td>
<td align="center">sheep</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2 id="普通名词和专有名词-Common-and-Proper-Nouns"><a href="#普通名词和专有名词-Common-and-Proper-Nouns" class="headerlink" title="普通名词和专有名词/ Common and Proper Nouns"></a>普通名词和专有名词/ Common and Proper Nouns</h2><p>区别是广义上/general 的东西与特定/specific 的一个具体东西</p>
<p>专有名词首字母大写</p>
<h3 id="eg-2"><a href="#eg-2" class="headerlink" title="eg:"></a>eg:</h3><table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="center">Common (general)</th>
<th align="center">Proper (specific)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody><tr>
<td align="center">city</td>
<td align="center">Chicago</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center">frog</td>
<td align="center">Kermit</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center">river</td>
<td align="center">Nile</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center">mountain</td>
<td align="center">Kilimanjaro</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2 id="具体名词和抽象名词-concrete-amp-abstract-nouns"><a href="#具体名词和抽象名词-concrete-amp-abstract-nouns" class="headerlink" title="具体名词和抽象名词/concrete &amp; abstract nouns"></a>具体名词和抽象名词/concrete &amp; abstract nouns</h2><p>Concrete 词源是 Con-crete，其中 Con- 意为 toghter，-crete 意为 grown，指代有实体的物质，something physical。</p>
<p>Abstract 词源是 Ab-stract，其中 Ab- 意为 away，-stract 意为 drawn，指代非物质的，not sphysical。</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>concrete nouns</th>
<th>abstract nouns</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody><tr>
<td>dog</td>
<td>sadness</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>ball</td>
<td>happiness</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>cliff</td>
<td>freedom</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>phone</td>
<td>permission</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2 id="不规则名词复数-f-变为-ves"><a href="#不规则名词复数-f-变为-ves" class="headerlink" title="不规则名词复数 f 变为 -ves"></a>不规则名词复数 f 变为 -ves</h2><table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>原形</th>
<th>复数形式</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody><tr>
<td>leaf</td>
<td>leaves</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>loaf</td>
<td>loaves</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>calf</td>
<td>calves</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2 id="不规则名词复数-以-en-结尾的单词"><a href="#不规则名词复数-以-en-结尾的单词" class="headerlink" title="不规则名词复数 以 en 结尾的单词"></a>不规则名词复数 以 en 结尾的单词</h2><p>英语是日耳曼语系</p>
<p>该规则只用与以下几个名词</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>原形</th>
<th>复数形式</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody><tr>
<td>child</td>
<td>children</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>ox</td>
<td>oxen</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<p>ox 是古英语单词，所以这条规则变化，而 box 则变为 boxes。</p>
<h2 id="不规则名词复数-基本复数形式"><a href="#不规则名词复数-基本复数形式" class="headerlink" title="不规则名词复数 基本复数形式"></a>不规则名词复数 基本复数形式</h2><p>即，名词的单复数形式一样。</p>
<p>one <strong>sheep</strong>, two <strong>sheep</strong>.</p>
<p>There was one sheep on the hill. There were two sheep on the hill.</p>
<p>fish 作为鱼的时候是单数形式同复数形式，作为物种的时候，复试形式是 fishes。</p>
<p>bison（野牛） 同 sheep。</p>
<h2 id="不规则名词复数-前部"><a href="#不规则名词复数-前部" class="headerlink" title="不规则名词复数 前部"></a>不规则名词复数 前部</h2><table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Language</th>
<th>Change</th>
<th>Singular</th>
<th>Irregular</th>
<th>Regplural(unformal)</th>
<th>means</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody><tr>
<td>Latin</td>
<td>-a → -ae</td>
<td>larva</td>
<td>larvae</td>
<td>larvas</td>
<td>幼虫</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Latin</td>
<td>-us → -i</td>
<td>fungus</td>
<td>fungi</td>
<td>funguses</td>
<td>真菌</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Latin</td>
<td>-um → -a</td>
<td>datum</td>
<td>data</td>
<td>-</td>
<td>数据</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Latin</td>
<td>-ex → -ix/-ices</td>
<td>index</td>
<td>indices</td>
<td>indexes</td>
<td>指数</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Greek</td>
<td>-is → -es</td>
<td>thesis</td>
<td>theses</td>
<td>thesises</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Greek</td>
<td>-on → -a</td>
<td>phenomenon</td>
<td>phenomena</td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
]]></content>
